node.text:
“Attending Southern University and A&M College was one of my best decisions. 

I remember being in Corporate America and folks that went to certain schools felt like they had a leg up. Especially the MBA’s. 

But now, I have received Entrepreneur of the Year awards from MBA organizations.

I have Ivy League folks wanting to intern. 

So moral of the story is, stick with your lane and do you.” 

What a powerful message from @_invstr 🙏🏾 Rep the HBCU that prepared you for the real world below!

node.text:
This is so dope! Winston-Salem State University (#WSSU) sophomore Rajah Caruth (@rajahcaruth_) has been signed as the first driver for Alpha Prime Racing. It’s a brand new venture between Caesar Bacarella and Tommy Joe Martins to form a new NASCAR Xfinity Series team in 2022. Caruth will be a part-time driver starting in the 2022 season. Caruth is currently obtaining his B.S. degree in Motorsports Management at WSSU. Black folks do it all!
